The paper deals with the compression of binary streams and information content measures, which are topics typically studied in information theory (cs.IT) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses algorithmic randomness (cs.CR) and computability (cs.CC), which are related fields. Finally, the paper provides an analogue of Shannon's source coding theorem, which is a fundamental result in machine learning and information theory, making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well.
